==English==

===Etymology===
Originally "to feel around", possibly metathesis of {{OE.}} ''[[græpsan]]'' "to touch, feel," from Proto-Germanic ''*graipison''.

===Verb===
'''to grasp''' ([[grasps]], [[grasped]], [[grasping]])

# To [[grip]]
# To [[understand]]

====Translations====
*Czech: [[stisknout]] (1), [[uchopit]] (1), [[pochopit]] (2)
*Dutch: [[grijpen]] (1), [[vastpakken]] (1), [[begrijpen]] (2)
*Spanish: [[agarrar]] (1), [[asir]] (1), [[comprender]] (2)
*Telugu: [[పట్టుకొను]] (pattukonu) (1), [[గ్రహించు]] (grahimchu) (2), [[ఆకళింపు చేసుకొను ]] (aakalimpu chesukonu) (2)

===Noun===
'''grasp'''

# [[grip]]
# [[understanding]]
# that which is [[accessible]]; that which is within one's [[reach]] or [[ability]]
#:''The goal is within my '''grasp'''.''

====Translations====
*Czech: [[uchopení]] (1), [[sevření]] (1), [[porozumění]] (2)
*Dutch: [[grip]] {{m}} (1), [[begrip]] {{n}} (2)
*Spanish: [[asimiento]] {{m}} (1), [[comprensión]] {{f}} (2)

